msgid "The \"Local Snapshots\" tab can be used to modify the schedule and pruning options on the local system. In other words, this is how often backups occur and how long to keep them. To configure a list of datasets to exclude from the snapshot, click the \"+\" button which will display the list of available datasets. Select a dataset to add it to the \"Excluded\" section. Repeat for any datasets that you do not wish to backup. To remove a dataset from the excluded list, so that it is added back to the snapshot schedule, highlight its entry in the \"Excluded\" section and click the \"-\" button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2478
msgid "The \"Replication\" tab, is shown in :numref:`Figure %s: Configuring Replication <lpreserver22>`."
msgstr ""

# 0f20d0bf22a5499988954f4d7f040e8d
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2484
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2479
msgid "If you wish to keep a copy of the snapshots on another system, this screen is used to indicate which system to send the snapshots to. Life Preserver supports two replication schemes:"
msgstr ""

# 5e5f977b6ef3485db63e3f718a9f4512
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2486
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2481
msgid "Replication to another system which is running the same version of ZFS and has SSH enabled. When this method is used, the replicated data is sent over an encrypted connection but is stored unencrypted on the other system. Refer to :ref:`Replication over SSH` for an example configuration."
msgstr ""

# 513a7756a9b34ad89d571ed2f6f947eb
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2489
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2484
msgid "Replication to an iSCSI target. This method provides the most security as the replicated data is sent over an encrypted connection and the data is stored in an encrypted format. The remote system does not need to be formatted with ZFS but it must understand kernel iSCSI and stunnel must be installed. Refer to :ref:`Replicating Encrypted Backups` for an example configuration."
msgstr ""

# 03515e517d5f4e4e811c7ef4be53e394
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2493
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2488
msgid "To exclude datasets from the snapshot from being replicated to the remote system, click the \"Excluded Data\" tab. This will let you create an exclude list as described in the \"Local Snapshots\" tab."
msgstr ""

# 4fb05ea1101246aca25d2e8aee5a1450
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2496
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2491
msgid "datasets which are excluded in the \"Local Snapshots\" tab are not backed up at all, and thus cannot be replicated. However, you do not have to replicate every dataset in the backup as you can use :menuselection:`Replication --> Excluded Data` to configure which datasets to exclude from the replication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2499
msgid "The \"Scrub\" tab, shown in :numref:`Figure %s: Modifying the Scrub Schedule <lpreserver23>`, can be used to modify the scrub schedule. It is a good idea to create a scrub schedule to verify the integrity of the ZFS pool. Typically, it is recommended to run a scrub once a week or before adding more disks to a pool. The status and results of a running scrub can be viewed from the command line by typing :command:`zpool status`. When viewing the results of the scrub, check to see if there were any errors, as this is typically an early indication of a failing disk. If you are getting errors, consider backing up your data and replacing the failing disk. Since a scrub is I/O intensive, it is recommended to schedule the scrub when the system is not in use, such as the early morning hours. Depending upon the size of the pool, the scrub may take some time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2510
msgid "The \"Restore Data\" tab, seen in :numref:`Figure %s: Viewing the Contents of the Snapshots <lpreserver8>`, is used to view the contents of the local snapshots. This allows you to easily restore any file which has been modified or deleted since a snapshot occurred."
msgstr ""

# 5ec658e1d6834384b3b38f2bc7c74812
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2517
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2511
msgid "In this example, the system has been configured to make a snapshot every 5 minutes. Since files have been modified on this system, the blue time slider bar indicates that several snapshots are available as a snapshot only occurs if changes have been made within the scheduled time increment. Click the arrows to go back or forward one snapshot at a time. Alternately, click the slider until you are viewing the desired time of the snapshot."
msgstr ""

# 3ad61ec7fc47441baeb0617dabc63f78
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2521
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2515
msgid "Once you have selected the desired date and time, use the drop-down menu to select the portion of the filesystem to view. In this example, the user has selected :file:`/usr/home/dru` as that is the user's home directory. The user can now expand the directory names to view the files within each directory."
msgstr ""

# 85056dddb98143078d42f66e827d614b
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2524
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2518
msgid "If your intent is to restore an earlier version of a file or a file that has been deleted, go back to the desired date and time, highlight the file, and click the \"Restore\" button. A copy of that file as it appeared at that point in time will be created in the same directory, with :file:`-reversion#` added to the filename. This way, any current version or restored version of the file will never be overwritten."
msgstr ""

# a7a56ebb84b645299aa4ff71c32ec391
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2528
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2522
msgid "The \"File\" menu contains the following options:"
msgstr ""

# 017fc46974964388b6cd067cc310ba95
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2530
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2524
msgid "**Manage Pool:** this will be greyed out if you have already configured your ZFS pool. If you have a second ZFS pool, you can select this option in order to start the Life Preserver Configuration Wizard for that pool."
msgstr ""

# 5e62b29970ce4a2ebda8a8cc70238c25
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2533
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2527
msgid "**Unmanage Pool:** if you wish to disable ZFS snapshots, select the ZFS pool name. Pop-up menus will ask if you are sure and then ask if you also want to delete the local snapshots from the system. If you choose to delete these snapshots, you will lose all of the older versions of the files contained in those backups. Once you have unmanaged a pool, you will need to use \"Manage Pool\" to rerun the Life Preserver Configuration Wizard for that pool."
msgstr ""

# 6827347abfc04458b140e95225a5d293
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2537
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2531
msgid "**Save Key to USB:** when you configure the replication of local snapshots to a remote system, you should immediately copy the automatically generated SSH key to a USB stick. Insert a FAT32 formatted USB stick and wait for :ref:`Mount Tray` to mount it. Then, click this option to copy the key."
msgstr ""

# bf6b306dc30042d1bc2cc583bdea3b7b
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2540
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2534
msgid "**Close Window:** closes the Life Preserver window. However, Life Preserver will continue to reside in the system tray."
msgstr ""

# da89ed29372148649d3176b7fa247831
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2542
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2536
msgid "The \"Classic Backups\" menu can be used to create an as-needed tarball of the user's home directory. This can be handy if you would like to make a backup of just your home directory in order to restore it in another directory or on another system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2545
msgid "To make a tar backup, click :menuselection:`Classic Backups --> Compress Home Dir` and select the name of the user. This will open the screen shown in :numref:`Figure %s: Backing Up a User's Home Directory <lpreserver9>`."
msgstr ""

# cc446c26f0c146b5956147bb7629dc92
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2552
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2546
msgid "If you want, you can change the filename of the archive to create. By default it will be in the format *username-YYYYMMDD-HHMM*. This screen also allows you to define which files to exclude from the backup. By default, it will exclude PBI shortcuts and, if it exists, the :file:`/bin` directory in the user's home directory. To exclude a specific file, click the white file icon to browse to the location of the file. To exclude a specific directory, click the blue directory icon to browse to the location of the directory."
msgstr ""

# 920f1441c4054756ab07b20b154eaf8e
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2557
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2551
msgid "Press \"Start\" to start the backup. A progress bar will indicate the status and size of the backup. Once the backup is complete, click the \"Finished\" button to exit this screen."
msgstr ""

# 7f26cea5055749bfacbe5cfdcd414ffd
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2560
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2554
msgid "Use :menuselection:`Classic Backups --> Extract Home Dir` to restore a previously made home directory backup. **Be sure this is what you want to do before using this option, as it will overwrite the current contents of the user's home directory.** If your goal is to restore files without destroying the current versions, use the \"Restore Data\" tab instead."
msgstr ""

# af29090caf974a3db677ff27902223e2
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2564
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2558
msgid "The \"Snapshots\" menu allows you to manage snapshots and replication outside of their configured schedules. If this menu is not visible, click :menuselection:`View -->Advanced` to enable it."
msgstr ""

# 7e5332429f264edb8aa1c7c6a2b8f62b
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2567
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2561
msgid "The \"Snapshots\" menu contains these options:"
msgstr ""

# 3e83fd1809c94f76989b4865ba9f78c3
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2569
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2563
msgid "**New Snapshot:** click this button to create a snapshot now, instead of waiting for the schedule. For example, you can create a snapshot before making changes to a file, so that you can preserve a copy of the previous version of the file. Or, you can create a snapshot as you make modifications to the system configuration. When creating a snapshot, a pop-up message will prompt you to input a name for the snapshot, allowing you to choose a name that is useful in helping you remember why you took the snapshot."
msgstr ""

# d4c4c29f7c96483cafeb5cc60675065d
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2574
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2568
msgid "**Delete Snapshot:** selecting this option will display the list of locally stored snapshots, listed in order from the oldest to the newest. If you select a snapshot, a warning will remind you that this is a permanent change that can not be reversed. In other words, the versions of files at that point in time will be lost."
msgstr ""

# 92ed40143ee545afb64eb0276d8fa9b8
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2578
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2572
msgid "**Start Replication:** this option will be greyed out if you have not yet configured replication to a remote server. To force a replication to a configured backup server, select the IP address of the remote system to start a replication now, rather than waiting for the scheduled time."
msgstr ""

# d0409ca588114df0b70e12e0a0ac3a12
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2581
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2575
msgid "**Re-Initialize Replications:** if a replication fails, it may prevent subsequent replications from completing successfully. In this case, select this option and select the IP address of the remote system in order to reset replication. After performing this re-initialization, click \"Start Replication\" to confirm that the replication issue has been resolved and snapshots are successfully replicating."
msgstr ""

# 6c0121202ec645e78c87b52555104f8e
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2585
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2579
msgid "The \"Disks\" menu provides the same functionality of :ref:`Mirroring the System to a Local Disk`, but from the GUI rather than the command line. You should read that section before attempting to use any of the disk options in this menu. It also lets you start and stop a ZFS scrub. If this menu is not visible, click :menuselection:`View -->Advanced` to enable it."
msgstr ""

# 9df884c958d04e628e59b19c8797bb73
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2589
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2583
msgid "The following options available in the \"Disks\" menu:"
msgstr ""

# 226816d30bdd4b6bb0a1e8ccaa67ab52
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2591
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2585
msgid "**Attach Disk:** if you wish to mirror another internal disk or an inserted external USB disk, select this option. The disk must be at least the same size as the PC-BSD® disk and you must be willing to have that disk be re-formatted. **Do not select this option if you have any data on the disk that you wish to keep.** This option is the GUI front-end to the :command:`lpreserver zpool attach` command."
msgstr ""

# 18bba04a676f4e3495baa440a15e11b4
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2596
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2590
msgid "**Detach Disk:** if you wish to remove an attached disk from the mirror, use this option. This option is the GUI front-end to the :command:`lpreserver zpool detach` command."
msgstr ""

# d56c3b41c3fd4df9b2606331ebce6800
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2599
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2593
msgid "**Set Disk Online/Offline:** if you need to temporarily disconnect or reconnect an attached external USB drive, select the appropriate option. This is the GUI equivalent to running :command:`lpreserver zpool offline` or :command:`lpreserver zpool online`."
msgstr ""

# 52fdd180c15d44f181eb65405a661b3c
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2602
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2596
msgid "**Start/Stop Scrub:** this option allows you to manually start a scrub now rather than waiting for the scrub schedule. If a scrub is currently running, you can stop it. Note that when you stop a scrub, it will need to start all over again the next time it is run."
msgstr ""

# 853ed31270834d03b3e55aa22c957ae9
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2609
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2603
msgid "Replication over SSH"
msgstr ""

# 75f5706ab4014ca39e1b7bcd7148d53d
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2611
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2605
msgid "Life Preserver can be configured to replicate snapshots to another system over an encrypted SSH connection. For this configuration, the remote system to hold a copy of the snapshots must meet the following requirements:"
msgstr ""

# c0d23ca8236d434abffc3de9ee61ccdc
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2614
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2608
msgid "The backup server **must be formatted with the latest version of ZFS,** also known as ZFS feature flags or ZFSv5000. Operating systems that support this version of ZFS include PC-BSD®, FreeBSD 9.2 or higher, and FreeNAS 9.1.x or higher."
msgstr ""

# c464368f4b14456194c9ed3f817055e5
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2617
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2611
msgid "That system must have SSH installed and the SSH service must be running. If the backup server is running PC-BSD®, SSH is already installed and you can start SSH using :ref:`Service Manager`. If that system is running FreeNAS® or FreeBSD, SSH is already installed, but you will need to start SSH."
msgstr ""

# 93f62d0587bb4c5e990ef3f81b1b3341
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2620
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2614
msgid "If the backup server is running PC-BSD®, you will need to open TCP port 22 (SSH) using :ref:`Firewall Manager`. If the server is running FreeBSD and a firewall has been configured, add a rule to open this port in the firewall ruleset. FreeNAS® does not run a firewall by default. Also, if there is a network firewall between the PC-BSD® system and the backup system, make sure it has a rule to allow SSH."
msgstr ""

# 457f05d33c734d7dbf33c5f25b70333a
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2624
#: ../../controlpanel.rst:2618
msgid "this configuration does not store the backup itself in an encrypted format. If you require that functionality, or prefer to backup to a system that is not formatted with ZFS, refer to :ref:`Replicating Encrypted Backups`."
msgstr ""

# 8f1f1d6b533d403aad47093089e5b079
